      "Incident Command System response activated",
      "IP transported to University Medical Center New Orleans"
    ],
    "summary": "On March 21, 2023, at approximately 16:45 hours, a rigger was injured during crane operations on the H&P 204 platform rig at Mississippi Canyon 809. The crew was staging a wireline riser (approximately 19 feet in length) with a red gate valve assembly into a transfer basket on the plus 50 level. During a blind lift using radio communication, as the upper end of the assembly was lowered, the lower end shifted and caught the rigger between the pipe and an adjacent basket. The rigger sustained a nondisplaced L4 fracture, traumatic hernia, and pelvic muscle tear. The incident occurred because the Designated Signal Person and rigging crew did not identify the pinch point hazard and the rigger positioned himself in a pinch point location between baskets in a congested workspace.",
